---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style lang="scss">
			.mugshot {
				width: 100%;
				max-width: 375px;
				height: auto;
				border-radius: 50%;
				object-fit: cover;
				@media (min-width: 1024px) {
					max-width: 100%;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<section id="home_intro" class="main main--home">
					
				<div class="main--home__content">
					<h3 class="main--home__intro">
						I swear that one day my portfolio will be online, maybe.
					</h3>
				<h1>
					<span><strong>Ciao, io sono Nico</strong>.</span> I'm an
					italian designer and fullstack developer living in Berlin,
					yet another one.
				</h1>
				<h1>
					<span>We could talk about a lot of things</span>
					<a href="mailto:m@nicovece.com">m@nicovece.com</a>
					<a href="tel:+4917686712451">+49 176 86712451</a>
					<a href="tel:+393791494041">+39 379 1494041</a>
					<!-- <a href="skype:nicovece?call">skype: nicovece</a> -->
				</h1>
				<h1>
					<span>I probably should work on my social media presence as
						well</span>
					<a href="https://github.com/nicovece">github</a>
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicovece/">linkedin</a>
					<a href="https://instagram.com/nicovece">instagram</a>
					<a href="https://mastodon.social/@nicovece">mastodon</a>
					<!-- <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/lightsumo/">flickr</a> -->
					<!-- <a href="https://twitter.com/nicovece">twitter</a> -->
				</h1>
				<h1 class="margin-top">
					<span>Feel free to poke around my <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}projects`} class="link--intext">projects</a> or get to know me a bit better by <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}#about-me`} class="link--intext">scrolling down</a></span>
				</h1>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section id="about-me" class="box--about bg--dark">
				<div class="box--about__left">	
					<img class="mugshot" src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}images/nico_vece.jpg`} alt="Nico" />
				</div>
				<div class="box--about__right">

	<h4><strong>Nico Vece</strong></h4>
	<aside>
		My full name is Nicola, but only my mom (when she's mad at me) and the tax office call me that, so let's stick with Nico.
	</aside>
	<h4>About me</h4>

  <p><strong>Digital product designer &amp; front-end developer with 20 years of experience, now transitioning into full-stack web development.</strong></p>

  <p>
    I design and build digital products end to end—where design, functionality, and code have to align and ship reliably.
    In 2025, I completed an intensive 8-month full-stack program (Jan–Oct) and added hands-on work with modern JavaScript frameworks,
    backend development, APIs, testing practices, and databases. I learn fast, take ownership, and focus on production-ready results.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>What I bring:</strong> professional maturity, a strong product mindset, and deep front-end fundamentals.
    I’m looking for a permanent full-stack role in Berlin (junior to mid-level), ideally on teams building modern web or AI/agentic products.
  </p>

  <h4>Tech snapshot</h4>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Strong:</strong> HTML5, CSS3, modern JavaScript (frontend), responsive UI implementation, component-based thinking</li>
    <li><strong>Currently working with:</strong> React, Angular, TypeScript, Node.js, Express, Python, Django, RESTful APIs, PostgreSQL &amp; SQLite (via ORMs), MongoDB, automated testing practices (Jest, Cucumber, Puppeteer)</li>
    <li><strong>Background / legacy:</strong> jQuery, PHP/WordPress, Bootstrap (legacy v3), Firebase, React Native (exposure)</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="about-cta" style="margin-top:1rem;">
    Open to a full-stack role in Berlin (hybrid/remote welcome) where I can contribute immediately on the frontend while deepening backend expertise and working on modern web or AI-driven products.
  </p>
	<a href="files/nico_vece-curriculum.pdf" class="text_link text_link--on_dark" download><strong>Download my CV</strong></a>

</div>
		</section>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
